The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | 4 held for murder
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      4 held for murder
          A STAFF REPORTER                               
	Four youths were arrested on Thursday for allegedly murdering a 16-year-old boy who worked as a help in a Bhowanipore flat on the suspicion that he had stolen a cellphone.         
	Feroze, Nandu, Yadav and Chand, in their late-20s and early-30s, were picked up from a highrise building on Lower Rawdon Street where Subodh Mondal used to work earlier.        
	Subodh was allegedly pushed off the fifth-floor terrace of the Bhowanipore building around 11pm on August 2. The boy from Bihar later died at SSKM Hospital.        
	Subodhs father had on Wednesday night lodged a four-page complaint with Bhowanipore police accusing the four of killing his son.        
	A help with whom Subodh used to work for a family living in the Lower Rawdon Street flat had alleged that the teenager used to steal mobile phones. This prompted the four  three drivers and a help  to hunt down Subodh, said an officer of Bhowanipore police station.         
	A relative of an accused said there was no evidence against him.                                                                                                                                                          
